Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community,
Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 1765/92 of 30 June 1992 establishing a support system for producers of certain arable crops(1), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 1624/98(2), and in particular Article 12 thereof,
(1) Whereas Commission Regulation (EC) No 1098/94(3), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 2528/98(4), lays down the regional base areas applicable under the support system for producers of certain arable crops;
(2) Whereas applications for conversion equivalent to 12979 ha have been submitted under Council Regulation (EC) No 1017/94 of 26 April 1994 concerning the conversion of land currently under arable crops to extensive livestock farming in Portugal(5), as amended by Regulation (EC) No 1461/95(6); whereas the basic area should be adjusted accordingly;
(3) Whereas it is therefore necessary to amend Regulation (EC) No 1098/94;
(4) Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Joint Management Committee for Cereals, Oils and Fats and Dried Fodder,
